points <- cbind(candisp$lon, candisp$lat)
str(points)
##  num [1:17, 1:2] -123 -123 -123 -123 -123 ...
pts   <- CRS("+proj=longlat +ellps=WGS84")
sp_pt <- SpatialPoints(points, proj4string = pts)
summary(sp_pt)
## Object of class SpatialPoints
## Coordinates:
##                  min        max
## coords.x1 -123.14595 -123.05526
## coords.x2   49.20938   49.29068
## Is projected: FALSE 
## proj4string : [+proj=longlat +ellps=WGS84]
## Number of points: 17
location <- get_map(location = c(lon = -123.043748, lat = 49.243522), zoom = 11, maptype = "hybrid")
## Map from URL : http://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/staticmap?center=49.243522,-123.043748&zoom=11&size=640x640&scale=2&maptype=hybrid&language=en-EN&sensor=false
location[2,1:4]
##      [,1]      [,2]      [,3]      [,4]     
## [1,] "#101F1B" "#101F1B" "#102424" "#102424"
fourCorners <- expand.grid(
  lon = as.numeric(attr(location, "bb")[, c("ll.lon", "ur.lon")]), 
  lat = as.numeric(attr(location, "bb")[, c("ll.lat", "ur.lat")])
)
# The inset_raster function needs 4 data coordinates. Pull it out of your "location" that you got via get_map
xmin <- attr(location, "bb")$ll.lon
xmax <- attr(location, "bb")$ur.lon
ymin <- attr(location, "bb")$ll.lat
ymax <- attr(location, "bb")$ur.lat

mp   <- ggplot(fourCorners, aes(x = lon, y = lat) ) + 
  inset_raster(location, xmin, xmax, ymin, ymax)  +
  geom_point(data=candisp, aes(x=lon,y=lat,color="red"),size=2)+
  ggtitle("Medicinal cannabis dispensaries \n in Lower Mainland")+
  scale_color_hue(guide='none')
  
mp
